1
00:00:31,625 --> 00:00:32,458
Behind you!

2
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:36,416
I call you,
Matthew the Apostle.

3
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:40,375
Publican, holy enemy of
magicians, and humble servant.

4
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,166
Ah, ahh!

5
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,625
Index!

6
00:00:45,458 --> 00:00:46,833
Damn!

7
00:00:49,708 --> 00:00:52,333
What are you doing,
Sister? Be careful!

8
00:00:52,416 --> 00:00:54,791
Uh-uh! It
wasn't me! I swear it!

9
00:00:54,875 --> 00:00:58,416
C-T-R-T-T-O-P.  A-O!

10
00:01:00,041 --> 00:01:01,166
[wimpers]

11
00:01:05,791 --> 00:01:07,833
Come on! If you
don't pay attention to

12
00:01:07,916 --> 00:01:09,208
what's around you,

13
00:01:09,291 --> 00:01:11,333
then you're that much
easier to defeat in battle.

14
00:01:11,416 --> 00:01:13,208
Did she just use
Spell Intercept?

15
00:01:13,291 --> 00:01:14,416
[distant whistle]

16
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,333
They've sounded
the retreat signal!

17
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:18,541
It's time to go,
Sister Angelene!

18
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:21,458
[ANGELENE] Right! Coming!

19
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:23,916
[KAMIJO groans]

20
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,916
[TATEMIYA] Now you have
seen it with your own eyes.

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,958
This is how they act when they
think that nobody is watching.

22
00:01:29,041 --> 00:01:31,833
[TATEMIYA] This is the true face
of the Roman Orthodox Church!

23
00:01:31,916 --> 00:01:41,916
♪ [Opening Song] ♪

24
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:06,916
[STIYL] If everything
the Amakusa said is true,


25
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,333
his last point
likely is, as well.


26
00:03:09,416 --> 00:03:12,791
It's very improbable they
will kill Orsola right away.

27
00:03:13,625 --> 00:03:14,791
There are
restrictions that will

28
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,583
make it difficult to do so.

29
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,458
What restricts
the Catholic Church?

30
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,375
[STIYL] Somebody deciphering
"The Book of the Law"

31
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:21,916
poses a threat to them.

32
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,500
However, Orsola Aquinas
is not guilty of anything.

33
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:27,125
[INDEX] "Thou shalt not
kill those who believe

34
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:29,541
the teachings of
God and of the Church."

35
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,541
So, if Orsola was
in no danger from them,

36
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:34,000
why were the Amakusa
worried about her safety?

37
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:36,166
[STIYL] Because of
the obvious exception.

38
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,083
They aren't allowed
to kill those who believe

39
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:40,250
the teachings of
God and the Church.

40
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,375
That gives them plenty
of latitude, though.

41
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:44,833
It means that they are
perfectly free to kill somebody

42
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:47,041
who has been excommunicated
from the Church for

43
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:50,375
not properly following their
teachings or honoring God.

44
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:51,583
The long and
short of it is,

45
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:53,458
they're going to label
her an enemy of God

46
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:55,416
and the Church so
they can kill her.

47
00:03:57,791 --> 00:03:59,583
But the power of a
grimoire is tainted.

48
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:02,500
It is something that can never
bring happiness to anybody.

49
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:04,166
It causes only conflict.

50
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:07,375
In its wake is a trail
of destruction and death.

51
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,458
Yeah, well screw that!

52
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,666
Unfortunately, it
doesn't matter now.

53
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:15,208
There's nothing more
that we can do to help her.

54
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:16,500
[KAMIJO] Erh!

55
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,875
Doesn't matter? You
know this is a human life

56
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:20,250
we're talking about?

57
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:21,708
No, what we're
talking about is

58
00:04:21,791 --> 00:04:24,083
the Roman Orthodox Church
applying their own rules

59
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,583
to one of their own people.

60
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,583
If we get more involved
than we already are,

61
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:29,375
it will mean starting
a religious war.

62
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:31,125
Is that what you want?

63
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,541
Of course not.

64
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:37,375
Don't worry so
much, young man.

65
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:38,875
Everything will be all right.

66
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:40,583
The English Puritans
may have no reason

67
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,416
to fight the Catholic
Church over this,

68
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,125
but the Amakusa
certainly do.

69
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:45,791
I was already planning
on paying their base

70
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:47,083
a little visit, anyway.

71
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:49,166
While I'm there rescuing
my own lost children,

72
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:51,333
I can save
Sister Orsola, as well.

73
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,416
Don't tell
me you plan on

74
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,916
going up against
them by yourself?

75
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,250
Hmph!

76
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,875
If I have to, then yes.

77
00:04:57,958 --> 00:04:59,625
That's exactly what I'll do.

78
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:08,333
[distant dog barking]

79
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,583
[STIYL] Okay, well I
guess that settles that.

80
00:05:11,666 --> 00:05:13,333
[STIYL] We should split
up and lay low for awhile

81
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:14,833
to be on the safe side.

82
00:05:14,916 --> 00:05:17,875
Once we get back to Academy
City, Index'll go with you.

83
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:19,500
[KAMIJO] Yeah, okay.

84
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:21,000
[STIYL] Oh.

85
00:05:21,083 --> 00:05:22,708
There is one thing
I want to ask you

86
00:05:22,791 --> 00:05:24,333
before we part ways, though.

87
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:25,708
Ask away.

88
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:28,416
The crucifix that I gave
you earlier during the fight.

89
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,500
[STIYL] You don't
seem to have it anymore.

90
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:31,458
[gasps]

91
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:32,875
Oh, sorry about that.

92
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:35,333
I gave it to Orsola,
and she's still got it.

93
00:05:35,416 --> 00:05:38,291
[KAMIJO] I... hope it
wasn't too expensive.

94
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,958
No, with something
like that,

95
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,708
the value lies in
having it with you.

96
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:46,000
It's okay. Our work
is done for the night,

97
00:05:46,083 --> 00:05:48,833
so it's nothing you
necessarily need right now.

98
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:51,041
[STIYL] Let's go.

99
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,083
Uh... right.

100
00:05:57,666 --> 00:06:05,833
♪

101
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,916
[KAMIJO] What am
I supposed to do?

102
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,958
Poor Orsola.

103
00:06:10,041 --> 00:06:12,958
There must have been something
more I could have done for her.

104
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:15,291
It's an issue for the
magicians to deal with.

105
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:17,041
You shouldn't feel
responsible for what happens

106
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,500
in a case like this.

107
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:19,958
Maybe.

108
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,166
[INDEX] You've already done
everything you need to do.

109
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,250
Now it's somebody else's turn.

110
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:27,541
You can't expect to solve every
problem in the world, you know.

111
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:31,333
[KAMIJO] I guess.

112
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:44,208
♪

113
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:45,708
[KAMIJO] Oh. I forgot.

114
00:06:45,791 --> 00:06:46,833
[INDEX] Hm?

115
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:49,000
Our refrigerator's
almost completely empty.

116
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:51,208
I'll find a convenience
store and get us something

117
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,583
to last the night.

118
00:06:52,666 --> 00:06:53,791
If you're going
to the store,

119
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:55,708
maybe we should
all go together.

120
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:56,958
[heavy exhale]

121
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,541
Do you even know where
the nearest store is?

122
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:00,708
Not really. Finding
it may take a while,

123
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:03,125
so you guys go on without me.

124
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:14,583
♪

125
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:18,416
[beeping]

126
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,666
[KAMIJO] Orsola's Church?

127
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,541
Yes. She did
excellent work spreading

128
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:27,000
the Church's teachings
throughout three heathen lands,

129
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:29,458
so she deserved to be
recognized appropriately.

130
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:31,416
[AGNESE] She was granted
special permission to oversee

131
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:34,083
the building of a church
that would bear her name.

132
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:37,333
I'm certain it must be
around here somewhere.

133
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:46,208
Auhhh!

134
00:07:48,875 --> 00:07:50,791
[wimpering]

135
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:52,791
[AGNESE] Come, now. You
really shouldn't make this

136
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:55,000
difficult for us, you know.

137
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:56,791
Unfortunately,
we do not have time to

138
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:59,166
draw this process out
the way that I would prefer.

139
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:01,291
Be grateful for that
and accept your punishment

140
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:03,166
without a fight. Uh!

141
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:04,708
[AGNESE] Are you listening?

142
00:08:04,791 --> 00:08:07,583
I said, are you
listening to me, sister?

143
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,916
[coughing]

144
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,166
Auhhh!

145
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:14,208
I have to admit I
almost feel sorry for you.

146
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:17,041
It's obvious that you have
no true friends to rely on.

147
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,041
If you did, you wouldn't
have fallen so readily

148
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:20,583
into the arms of
the Amakusa Church

149
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,541
simply because
they offered to help.

150
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:24,166
The Amakusa and
the English Puritans

151
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:25,666
are both unworthy.

152
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,625
I find it disgusting
that they would ever dare

153
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,708
to include themselves
as church of the cross.

154
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:32,125
You were weak, and
now you are going to

155
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:33,875
reap the reward
for putting your life

156
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,541
into such incompetent hands.

157
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:37,625
It took very little
convincing on our part.

158
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:41,250
They were easily duped
into bringing us our quarry.

159
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:44,458
[ORSOLA] You said
they were duped?

160
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:46,583
You mean you lied to them?

161
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:49,916
You deceived them, and
that's why they helped you?

162
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,416
[AGNESE] That's right.

163
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:54,958
[ORSOLA] Then that means they
weren't working with you.

164
00:08:55,041 --> 00:08:56,625
You tricked them!

165
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,750
I don't see how that
makes any difference!

166
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,458
They personally delivered
the woman they were

167
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,958
supposed to protect
into enemy hands.

168
00:09:04,041 --> 00:09:06,208
Your friends are beyond hope.

169
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:11,333
I suppose we'll
have to disagree.

170
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:14,458
[AGNESE] Hey! What
are you smiling about?

171
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:17,958
[ORSOLA] Am I smiling?
Well, why shouldn't I?

172
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:19,583
After all...

173
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:23,333
You have just given
me a very precious gift.

174
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:24,750
[ORSOLA] You helped
me realize something

175
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,750
I didn't know until now.

176
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,791
Your words and actions
have revealed to me

177
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:31,958
the true nature of the
Roman Orthodox Church.

178
00:09:32,041 --> 00:09:33,541
What?

179
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:35,958
[ORSOLA] The ones
who helped me earlier,

180
00:09:36,041 --> 00:09:39,500
they act on what they believe
with their innermost hearts.

181
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:44,166
Whether it be a person,
or a thought, or a feeling.

182
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:47,500
If they believe in something,
then they will fight for it.

183
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:51,916
By contrast, where
they act on their beliefs...

184
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:55,083
we, sisters, act on
our fears and our doubts.

185
00:09:55,166 --> 00:09:58,000
And what an ugly thing
that has turned out to be.

186
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,125
[wimper]

187
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,958
[AGNESE] If you
want to die so badly,

188
00:10:02,041 --> 00:10:04,583
by all means, continue talking.

189
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:05,875
[ORSOLA] Ahuhhh!

190
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:06,958
[AGNESE] But as you breathe
your last breath,

191
00:10:07,041 --> 00:10:08,416
know who is responsible.

192
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,541
Regardless of what you
think, the blame lies

193
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:12,916
on the shoulders of
those who brought you here.

194
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,666
[ORSOLA] Is that so?

195
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:18,000
And just what am I
supposed to blame them for?

196
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:19,125
[AGNESE] Everything.

197
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:21,375
Once again, we see
things differently.

198
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:25,250
They had no personal reason
to involve themselves in this.

199
00:10:26,041 --> 00:10:28,458
But even so, they
came rushing to the aid

200
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:30,416
of a complete stranger.

201
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,625
They put their lives in
danger in order to help me.

202
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:39,333
[ORSOLA] Tell me, can there be
any act more worthy of praise?

203
00:10:39,416 --> 00:10:43,333
Because if there is, I
certainly cannot think of it.

204
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:45,083
And you expect
me to lay blame

205
00:10:45,166 --> 00:10:47,541
on the shoulders
of these people?

206
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:51,125
The people who gave me
the most magnificent gift

207
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:53,500
I could ever receive.

208
00:10:56,125 --> 00:10:57,916
[gasping]

209
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:04,708
How could anyone possibly
get past our barriers?

210
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:07,333
[AGNESE] Damn!
Which organization?

211
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:22,541
♪

212
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:24,291
[AGNESE] Hmph. You
expect me to wonder how

213
00:11:24,375 --> 00:11:27,416
you managed that, but I
think I might have an idea.

214
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,416
My guess is you have
something in your possession

215
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,666
with the power to
neutralize our barrier.

216
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:33,666
Well, did I guess correctly?

217
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:35,916
[KAMIJO] I don't
enjoy being lied to.

218
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,583
So, I suggest that
you don't do it again.

219
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,208
[AGNESE]
What would be the point?

220
00:11:40,291 --> 00:11:42,125
At this juncture, it should
be pretty clear to you

221
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:44,083
what's happening here. Right?

222
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:45,750
[AGNESE] The English
Puritans realized they have

223
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,833
no place in this and ran off.

224
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,958
So why is it you
haven't given up yet?

225
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:53,250
Come now.
This is your last chance.

226
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:55,500
Your fate hangs in the balance.

227
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:57,958
I think you know
what you ought to do.

228
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,458
[KAMIJO] Yeah, you're right.

229
00:11:59,541 --> 00:12:02,291
This is my last chance
to do what I need to.

230
00:12:02,375 --> 00:12:04,125
I am very
well aware of that.

231
00:12:04,208 --> 00:12:05,416
Well, in that case...

232
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,750
[running footsteps]

233
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:08,625
[KAMIJO grunts]

234
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:13,333
You filthy heathen!

235
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:15,583
What exactly do
you think you're doing?

236
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:19,500
[KAMIJO] What I ought
to do, obviously. Come on!

237
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:21,166
Stop playing the idiot.

238
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:23,958
I came here to rescue her!

239
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:26,833
I admit, I find you...
fascinating.

240
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:28,291
Go on, take a look around.

241
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:30,958
How much do you really think
you can accomplish alone?

242
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:33,500
Maybe you would like to
give us a demonstration?

243
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:37,583
[weapons clinking]

244
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:39,041
[fire roaring]

245
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:41,083
[NUNS screaming]

246
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:48,208
How rude. You just had
to start without me, huh?

247
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,250
Why are you here?

248
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:51,541
What? The English
Puritan Church?

249
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:52,916
[AGNESE] You should go.

250
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,791
This is a matter for the
Roman Orthodox Church alone.

251
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:58,958
You don't want to interfere in
our internal affairs, do you?

252
00:12:59,041 --> 00:13:02,958
No, but as it turns out,
this isn't actually so internal.

253
00:13:03,041 --> 00:13:06,000
[STIYL] Look at
Orosla Aquinas' chest.

254
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,458
You do see that
English Puritan crucifix

255
00:13:08,541 --> 00:13:10,416
that's hanging there, don't you?

256
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:14,250
She has asked someone
to place it around her neck.

257
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:18,958
That act signifies an acceptance
of English Puritan protection.

258
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:22,375
Orsola Aquinas is no
longer a Roman Catholic.

259
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:27,041
In fact, she is now a member
of the English Puritan Church.

260
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:28,583
I get it.

261
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:30,083
So, that means...

262
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:31,541
[AGNESE] Hm! Do
you honestly think

263
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:33,541
that kind of sophistry
will work here?

264
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:35,791
[STIYL]
Not entirely, no. However...

265
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:38,333
I'm sure you realize that
if you plan to submit her

266
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:41,250
to an inquisition,
there will be consequences.

267
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,916
Now that she's one of us,
the English Puritan Church

268
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,208
cannot stand by and do nothing.

269
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:52,250
[STIYL] Given that,
I hope you'll think twice

270
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,666
before turning your
blades against her.

271
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,125
Or have you mistaken me
for a man so chivalrous

272
00:13:57,208 --> 00:14:00,333
he won't fight a woman when
the situation calls for it?

273
00:14:00,416 --> 00:14:02,833
Uh! Fine, so we fight
two instead of one.

274
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,208
[TATEMIYA] It would
be unwise to assume

275
00:14:04,291 --> 00:14:05,708
it's just the two of them.

276
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:10,125
[TATEMIYA] I get
that you're not really

277
00:14:10,208 --> 00:14:11,583
the smartest kid in the world,

278
00:14:11,666 --> 00:14:14,750
but you don't have to ask
what I'm doing here, do you?

279
00:14:15,708 --> 00:14:17,416
Tatemiya?

280
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,333
[TATEMIYA] And here I thought
we'd arranged our plans

281
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:22,375
with the Puritans so carefully,
acting quickly so we could

282
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,625
get here before you
decided to play the hero

283
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:26,541
and make a move on your own.

284
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:29,833
Clearly, you're an even bigger
fool than I had imagined.

285
00:14:29,916 --> 00:14:30,916
[chuckles]

286
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,041
But, hey, at least
you're foolishness

287
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:33,958
is always fun to watch.

288
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:36,250
[INDEX] You know,
Toma, when I said this

289
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,458
wasn't your responsibility,
I was hoping you'd

290
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,958
take the hint and butt
out for once in your life.

291
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:42,458
[KAMIJO] Good to see you, too.

292
00:14:42,541 --> 00:14:45,708
[INDEX] But now you've
left us no choice, have you?

293
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:48,000
We're all here, aren't we?

294
00:14:48,083 --> 00:14:51,375
So what do you say we
save Sister Orsola together?

295
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:54,458
Yeah!

296
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,666
Go! Kill the heathens!

297
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,791
[yelling]

298
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:22,708
[KAMIJO] Come on, let's go!
Do you think you'll be okay?

299
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:25,291
I'm fine.
She didn't do much.

300
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:28,416
Nothing that I can't
bear for now, anyway.

301
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:32,041
[KAMIJO]
She's amazing. So brave.

302
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:34,208
If I ever needed
a reason to fight...

303
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:35,500
I've got one now.

304
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:45,708
♪

305
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:47,500
[yelling]

306
00:15:51,708 --> 00:15:53,500
Oh, uh. Thanks a lot!

307
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:58,083
Hmmm.

308
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:00,375
[TSUCHIMIKADO chuckles]

309
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:03,833
You up here for appreciation,
inspiration, or exhilaration?

310
00:16:03,916 --> 00:16:05,416
Or all three, maybe?

311
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:06,916
Tsuchimikado.

312
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,000
C'mon, it's a
relief, isn't it?

313
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:11,375
Finding out that your old
pals weren't part of a plot

314
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:13,833
to kidnap Orsola and
use "The Book of the Law"

315
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:16,583
for their own nefarious
ends. That must be nice.

316
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:19,250
Right, you like the
sound of your own voice.

317
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:21,250
Why do I get the feeling
that you and your employers

318
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:23,666
were hoping to use
this opportunity to snatch

319
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:26,083
"The Book of the Law"
out from under them?

320
00:16:26,166 --> 00:16:27,708
Hm.

321
00:16:27,791 --> 00:16:28,625
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
You know the whole story

322
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:30,291
up to this point, right?

323
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:32,166
The Amakusa Church
did not, in fact,

324
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,833
steal "The Book of the Law."

325
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:37,333
That was a false charge
fabricated by the Catholics.

326
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:40,041
Which means... there was
never any need to bring

327
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:43,583
the Book all the way
here in the first place.

328
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:46,458
The Book that was brought
into this country is a phony.

329
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:48,166
The original
text remains hidden

330
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:51,083
deep in the stacks
of the Vatican Library.

331
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:53,916
So... are you satisfied now?

332
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:56,791
Hmph. Yes, I am.

333
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:59,708
As long as he's leading
them, they'll be fine.

334
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:01,666
[KANZAKI] The Amakusa
will follow the right path,

335
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,125
even without me.

336
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:08,291
[KAMIJO breathing heavily]

337
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:16,916
♪

338
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:17,666
[KAMIJO] Huahhh!

339
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,041
[NUN wimpers]

340
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:23,416
[ALL grunting]

341
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,416
Uh!

342
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:29,125
[KAMIJO] Ahhh!

343
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:34,250
[BOTH groaning]

344
00:17:39,916 --> 00:17:42,500
[ORSOLA] Oh! That was quite
a fall. Are you alright?

345
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,750
I think... so.

346
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:54,291
Damn her!

347
00:17:55,041 --> 00:18:01,291
[weapons clinking]

348
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:11,333
♪

349
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,375
Huh?

350
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:24,166
Ahhh--Uh!

351
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:31,583
♪

352
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:33,625
So many of them
taking on one little girl?

353
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:35,083
I don't think so!

354
00:18:35,166 --> 00:18:36,208
[STIYL] No, stop!

355
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,750
[NUNS scream]

356
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:42,125
[STIYL] We don't want to get too
close to her right now, Amakusa.

357
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,833
[STIYL] If we interfere,
she won't be able to do

358
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:46,041
what she needs to as easily.

359
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,083
Haaahhh!

360
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:52,166
[NUNS scream]

361
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:53,500
[NUNS groan]

362
00:18:53,583 --> 00:18:56,500
Whoa. What did
she just do to them?

363
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:06,208
[STIYL] That is "Sheol Fear."
It's a song that uses

364
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:07,916
all of the knowledge
that is laid out in the

365
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,833
one hundred and
three thousand volumes

366
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:13,416
and denounces the contradictions
those doctrines contain.

367
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:16,083
[STIYL] That song is a strong
defense against those who

368
00:19:16,166 --> 00:19:18,125
blindly follow
doctrines of faith without

369
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:20,250
considering what is right.

370
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:23,458
[STIYL] Upon hearing it, their
minds collapse in on themselves,

371
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:25,333
albeit temporarily.

372
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:29,333
[STIYL] Grimoires are
not simply texts to be read.

373
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:32,916
Even without any magical power,
she has mastered the volumes.

374
00:19:35,458 --> 00:19:37,958
I doubt there could ever be
a better candidate than her

375
00:19:38,041 --> 00:19:41,083
to serve as the
librarian for the grimoires.

376
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,125
What I'd like to
know is if she had

377
00:19:43,208 --> 00:19:44,541
this kind of trick
up her sleeve,

378
00:19:44,625 --> 00:19:47,625
why didn't she use it
before things got ugly?

379
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,000
It is a peculiar attack.

380
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:52,375
[STIYL] It works on what
is called the "group mind,"

381
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:55,083
breaking down
collective mental barriers.

382
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:57,208
Accordingly, the
make-up of that group mind

383
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:59,166
is a factor to consider.

384
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:01,125
[NUNS screaming]

385
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:04,500
[STIYL] For example,
when we were fighting

386
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:07,208
your people earlier, Kamijo
and I were in the way,

387
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:08,625
so the purity was diminished,

388
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,666
and the attack would've
performed poorly.

389
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:11,916
[TATEMIYA] Well, I'm
glad that we weren't on

390
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,916
the receiving end of that.

391
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:18,166
[rumbling]

392
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:21,208
[chatter]

393
00:20:21,291 --> 00:20:23,250
[ANGELENE] We shouldn't be here!

394
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:25,916
Stop clucking like
a bunch of scared hens.

395
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,208
[AGNESE] You're only
making fools of yourselves.

396
00:20:28,291 --> 00:20:30,458
Especially you,
Sister Angelene.

397
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:31,541
[ANGELENE] It's just
that I'm worried about

398
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:33,125
our fellow sisters.

399
00:20:33,208 --> 00:20:35,958
It's been more than ten minutes
since the fighting got underway.

400
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,541
It should have
been over by now,

401
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,833
but it keeps getting
more intense out there.

402
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:42,375
And what's worse is we
don't know what's happening.

403
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:45,125
There! See?

404
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:46,458
[ANGELENE] Was that
explosion just now

405
00:20:46,541 --> 00:20:48,333
caused by our side or theirs?

406
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:51,333
There's no way for us to know
when we're waiting in here.

407
00:20:52,541 --> 00:20:55,041
[ANGELENE] Please, don't you
think we should do something?

408
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:57,833
They can use all the
help we can give them!

409
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:59,458
[sighs]

410
00:20:59,541 --> 00:21:01,375
[AGNESE] Very well. I release
you from your detail

411
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:02,708
as my bodyguard.

412
00:21:02,791 --> 00:21:04,833
You may go outside and
join the lines of battle.

413
00:21:04,916 --> 00:21:08,875
Oh! Thank you Sister Agnese,
we won't let you down!

414
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:17,083
♪

415
00:21:17,166 --> 00:21:19,416
That filth
cannot avoid justice.

416
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,500
[AGNESE] There will
be no escape for them.

417
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:24,416
Those who do evil
shall be punished.

418
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,208
Such is the way of the Church.

419
00:21:28,125 --> 00:21:29,333
[NUN screams]

420
00:21:29,416 --> 00:21:31,250
[NUNS scream]

421
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:44,833
Forget about defense.
Sisters, we must attack.

422
00:21:44,916 --> 00:21:46,583
[LUCIA] We must do
what is necessary to

423
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:48,958
defeat the enemies
of the Church.

424
00:21:55,458 --> 00:21:58,208
[INDEX] Some kind
of magical attack?

425
00:22:01,916 --> 00:22:03,708
[gasps]

426
00:22:03,791 --> 00:22:10,583
♪

427
00:22:10,666 --> 00:22:13,708
[INDEX] Did they? That's crazy!

428
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:18,125
[INDEX] They would go that far.
Just to avoid the Sheol Fear?

429
00:22:18,208 --> 00:22:25,291
♪

430
00:22:26,083 --> 00:22:36,041
♪ [Ending Song] ♪

431
00:23:57,291 --> 00:23:59,125
[KAMIJO] The final
battle has begun.

432
00:23:59,208 --> 00:24:02,041
We are surrounded on all
sides, under constant attack.

433
00:24:02,125 --> 00:24:04,416
Is there any way to
get out of this alive?

434
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:06,583
Next time, "Lotus Wand."

435
00:24:06,666 --> 00:24:09,791
When science and magic
cross paths, a story is born.

